The couplet is the maqta' (opening/radif-establishing sher) of **Diwan-E-Ghalib chapter 153**:

> **Naqsh faryadi hai kis ki shokhi-e-tehreer ka**
> **Kaaghazi hai pairahan har paikar-e-tasveer ka**

*"Whose playful script does this whole painted world complain of? / Each figure wears the paper robes a petitioner is made of."*

The key: **naqsh** (painted image) is **faryadi** (complainant/petitioner) of the artist's **shokhi-e-tehreer** (mischievous/playful pen), and every figure in a painting wears **kaaghazi pairahan** — "paper robes" — meaning the painted figures on paper are themselves the complainants against the artist's mischief. This is the couplet the question paraphrases.
